<item>
            <title>[LU-996] add standard &quot;user&quot; mount option to mount.lustre</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-996</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The parsing of the &quot;user&quot; mount option by mount_lustre.c is missing.  The opt_map[] entry for &quot;nouser&quot; exists and is correct, but the &quot;user&quot; mount option does not exist.  There may be technical or security reasons why non-root users cannot mount a Lustre filesystem, but I don&apos;t recall the details at this time.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
